Content:
Rust update summary: 

New BP system:  It might come in next forcewipe. Basic stuff is locked, and BPs are required for them to be unlocked (as you are aware). BUT complete items can be found in radtowns and items can be learned with enough scrap in a research bench. They also require components. Additionally you can trade it via vending machines. 3  workbenches will also be required in order for making high-end items (tier 3 workbench for ak, c4, etc even if you have the mats for it). Building one requires parts from one-another, and workbenches increace crafting speed for stuff below their tier.  (like making a hoodie in a tier 3 workbench will make it take half as long, which is GREAT for mass-crafting and stuff).  Loot tables will be changed. 

 twig raid nerf: Stairs do not work  and only roofs work. Ladders still work. This makes  compounds more viable (although not the best, unless you layer walls or something. Its still a lot better than it was last time. Also barracades will not completely block ladder placement. 

Minor details:  You can put shelves under existing chests. You can't paint on mountans. Furnaces can be placed in pre-built furnace bases. Cars have headlights with  F, and breaklighs. They also have better collision models. Playermodels are being deveoped. Hair is also coming.  The invisible fire from heli crates/apc crates.  Grills may come too.

   RAML2       : origin = 0x008C00, length = 0x000400
   RAML3       : origin = 0x009000, length = 0x001000

   GPIOCTRL    : origin = 0x006F80, length = 0x000040     /* GPIO control registers */
   GPIODAT     : origin = 0x006FC0, length = 0x000020     /* GPIO data registers */
   GPIOINT     : origin = 0x006FE0, length = 0x000020     /* GPIO interrupt/LPM registers */
}


SECTIONS
{

}

Author: linuxguy11#3353
Content:
```
ABCco8r2 Microcode

2 bytes
1st byte - Instruction
2nd byte - Parameter

0x00, NOP - Do nothing
0x01, RRD <r1> - Puts register <r1> contents on bus
0x02, RWR <r1> - Writes data on bus to register <r1>
0x03, SET <val> - Sets bus to <val>
0x04, JZE <loc> - Jumps to <loc> if bus is zero
0x05, JNZ <loc> - Jumps to <loc> if bus isn't zero 
0x06, HLT - Halts CPU and waits for an interrupt
0x07, PCI - Increments program counter (thus stopping microcode execution)
```
